<h3>ALLIED ASSOCIATIONS BRING FULL SCOPE OF CONSUMER ELECTRONICS TO THE 2006 INTERNATIONAL CES</h3>

	<h4>More than 90 International and U.S.-Based Association Supporters Contribute to Diversity</h4>

<br>
<em>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/20/2005</em>
<br><br>
With organizations representing broadcasters, content, distribution, manufacturers 

and other international industries, the Allied Association program will converge once again at the 2006 International CES&#174, bringing together a record-breaking 92 organizations from the entire breadth of the consumer technology industry. The 2006 

International CES, the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow, returns to Las Vegas, January 5-8, 2006.
<p>
      "The organizations participating in the Allied Association program at CES represent a diverse range of companies 

committed to improving and growing the consumer electronics industry," said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO of CEA, the 

producer of the International CES. "As the program continues to expand, we are honored by the growing number of dedicated 

participants, including an extensive lineup of international organizations, including representatives from Australia, Canada, 

China, India, Israel, Malaysia and Taiwan."  
<p>
      Organizations participating in the International CES' Allied Association program will have a presence at CES and access 

to the Allied Association lounge with a business center, meeting rooms and other VIP opportunities, located in room S220 at 

the LVCC and the upper level lobby at Innovations Plus at the Sands. 

<p>
